snippet.title: BattleVR - Prototype Phase 3
snippet.description:
This is the first time I am showing the space fighter I am working one. There is no sound in this video because GearVR's native recording only does video right now. 

The end goal for this project is to have an open-source space fighter game for VR. Currently I am working on getting the foundations ready before I work on things like 3d models/music/effects and other, although I am using just some place holder 3d models, sounds and music.

What I currently have is:
- Multiplayer game with UI for creating/joining games
- 6-Degrees of Freedom physics
- One projectile type exists but more types are supported
- UI for creating/joining game, pausing   
- If you destroy the enemy capital ship, you win the game

Repo: https://github.com/CRamsan/BattleVR
Wiki: https://github.com/CRamsan/BattleVR/wiki

snippet.title: Prototype - Grid based movement on empty level
snippet.description:
Prototype that I made because I just remembered that I used to play Doom RPG a lot back on my Sony Ericsson phone.

Doom RPG is played on a turn based system, every time you move, all other NPCs will move as well. The original game also involve lots of RPG elements like talking with NPCs and leveling up your stats.

This demo is just for the grid turn movement, interacting with doors and some basic lighting conditions.
